♪ Baby, I know pain
I'm Dr. Browne.

00:12.229 --> 00:13.752
I'll be performing
your surgery today.

00:13.796 --> 00:15.208
I'm Dr. Browne.
I'll be performing
your surgery today.

00:15.232 --> 00:17.234
♪ I just thought
it didn't rain

00:17.278 --> 00:18.322
Dr. Browne...

00:18.366 --> 00:19.454
♪ In California

00:19.497 --> 00:21.499
I'll be performing
your surgery today.

00:21.543 --> 00:22.892
♪ Baby, I know love

00:22.935 --> 00:24.198
It's a very simple procedure.

00:25.503 --> 00:27.288
It's a straightforward
procedure.

00:27.331 --> 00:31.857
♪ 'Cause I've never known
love like this before

00:31.901 --> 00:33.294
It was a successful surgery.

00:35.339 --> 00:38.560
♪♪

00:38.603 --> 00:40.518
♪ Baby, I know dreams

00:40.562 --> 00:42.303
♪ Tend to crumble at extremes

00:42.346 --> 00:44.261
The surgery was a success.

00:44.305 --> 00:46.002
♪ I just thought
our dream would last

00:46.046 --> 00:49.310
We expect a full recovery.

00:49.353 --> 00:51.312
♪ We're surviving,
we're still living ♪

00:51.355 --> 00:54.445
I expect a full recovery.

00:54.489 --> 00:55.707
Baby.

00:56.969 --> 00:57.970
Where do you want this?

00:59.798 --> 01:00.886
Uh, thanks, Mom.

01:00.930 --> 01:02.018
Uh, put it by my bag.

01:02.062 --> 01:03.382
I'll have the hospital lab
run it.

01:13.812 --> 01:17.033
Nausea and severe
abdominal pain after eating.

01:17.077 --> 01:19.035
This patient could need
a lap chole.

01:19.079 --> 01:21.037
That would be
an ideal first surgery.

01:21.081 --> 01:22.821
Let's not get
ahead of ourselves.

01:22.865 --> 01:24.519
She may just need an antacid.

01:26.738 --> 01:27.783
Hi, Michelle.

01:27.826 --> 01:29.828
I understand your mother
is on her way in.

01:29.872 --> 01:32.048
I'm Dr. Browne.
And I'm Dr. Shaun Murphy.

01:32.092 --> 01:33.702
You need to fix my sister.

01:33.745 --> 01:35.269
What's your name?

01:35.312 --> 01:37.401
Tisha. Hi, Tisha.

01:37.445 --> 01:38.726
Well, that is exactly
why we're here...

01:38.750 --> 01:40.274
To help your sister.

01:40.317 --> 01:41.318
Fostersister.

01:42.493 --> 01:43.625
When did the pain start?

01:43.668 --> 01:44.887
About an hour ago.

01:44.930 --> 01:46.845
It was on the bus.

01:46.889 --> 01:50.588
My sister rides with me
every day to school and back.

01:50.632 --> 01:53.548
My brother and I
used to live on a bus.

01:53.591 --> 01:54.766
Cool.

01:54.810 --> 01:55.724
Have you felt like this before?

01:55.767 --> 01:57.117
A few times.

01:59.423 --> 02:00.816
Ow.

02:00.859 --> 02:03.427
She has extreme upper-right
quadrant tenderness.

02:03.471 --> 02:06.517
That's consistent
with cholecystitis.

02:06.561 --> 02:10.304
As is her fever
and elevated white count.

02:10.347 --> 02:12.915
Your gallbladder probably
needs to be removed.

02:12.958 --> 02:15.091
♪♪

02:15.135 --> 02:16.527
You must be excited, Claire.

02:16.571 --> 02:18.442
This is going to be
your first surgery.

02:18.486 --> 02:21.228
♪♪

02:21.271 --> 02:22.794
Has your urine changed color?

02:22.838 --> 02:24.405
Gotten darker?

02:36.547 --> 02:39.855
I hear Dr. Browne might have
landed her first lap chole.

02:39.898 --> 02:42.162
It's not exactly
a straightforward case.

02:42.205 --> 02:43.902
The duct is massively dilated,

02:43.946 --> 02:46.427
the wall's inflamed,
this scarring...

02:46.470 --> 02:48.603
It's gonna limit visibility.

02:48.646 --> 02:49.971
Well, the thickness
of the gallbladder wall

02:49.995 --> 02:52.259
does pose a challenge.

02:52.302 --> 02:53.303
What do you think?

02:54.261 --> 02:55.610
It's not her decision.

02:55.653 --> 02:56.773
It's mine, as the attending.

02:58.395 --> 03:00.180
Doesn't mean she shouldn't
offer her opinion.

03:04.445 --> 03:08.144
I think that, um,
Dr. Melendez is right.

03:08.188 --> 03:10.146
With the limited visibility,
I shouldn't be...

03:10.190 --> 03:13.454
Only with a laparoscopic
cholecystectomy.

03:13.497 --> 03:16.283
Which I don't think
we should do.

03:16.326 --> 03:18.720
An open procedure
would provide a clearer view

03:18.763 --> 03:20.393
of the gallbladder
and the surrounding anatomy

03:20.417 --> 03:22.027
despite the inflammation.

03:29.731 --> 03:31.820
Carly and I went on
another date last night.

03:31.863 --> 03:32.864
Mm. What did you do?

03:32.908 --> 03:34.257
Dinner, movie...

03:34.301 --> 03:36.651
We walked 12 minutes to a deli

03:36.694 --> 03:38.043
and had some food and talked.

03:39.131 --> 03:40.437
Where are we going?

03:40.481 --> 03:42.961
Andrews is starting
an open chole.

03:43.005 --> 03:44.069
Sounds like
it's going well
with you and Carly.

03:44.093 --> 03:45.181
Oh, yes.

03:45.225 --> 03:48.010
She answered
all of my questions.

03:48.053 --> 03:49.403
How many did you ask?

03:49.446 --> 03:52.362
83, although some had
multiple parts.

03:53.929 --> 03:55.713
"Do you want to have children?

03:55.757 --> 03:57.628
If yes,
how many and when?"

03:57.672 --> 03:59.108
"Where do you plan
to raise them?

03:59.151 --> 04:01.850
In what
religious tradition?"

04:01.893 --> 04:04.113
Those are pretty intense.

04:04.156 --> 04:07.551
They're good questions,
Claire,
about important topics.

04:07.595 --> 04:10.424
Early on,
people usually stick
with lighter stuff...

04:10.467 --> 04:12.861
Favorite movies, bands,
hometowns.

04:12.904 --> 04:13.688
Small talk.

04:13.731 --> 04:16.473
♪♪

04:16.517 --> 04:19.084
Put some LAPs
in the upper-right quadrant.

04:21.348 --> 04:22.262
Here's the Bovie,
Dr. Andrews.

04:22.305 --> 04:24.742
Isn't the point of dating

04:24.786 --> 04:27.528
to gather information
to determine compatibility?

04:27.571 --> 04:29.225
Retract the omentum.

04:29.269 --> 04:30.879
Sure.

04:30.922 --> 04:33.577
Isn't that best achieved

04:33.621 --> 04:36.232
by finding out
what's important
to the other person?

04:36.276 --> 04:38.321
Hemostats.

04:38.365 --> 04:39.888
It's a...
It's a process, Shaun,

04:39.931 --> 04:41.019
like peeling an onion.

04:41.063 --> 04:42.891
People are more comfortable

04:42.934 --> 04:44.980
revealing their layers
gradually,

04:45.023 --> 04:47.023
as opposed to getting sliced
right down the middle.

04:47.504 --> 04:48.897
I heard Dr. Lim selected you

04:48.940 --> 04:51.029
for the first lead.

04:51.073 --> 04:53.031
I'm guessing you drew
a cholecystectomy.

04:53.075 --> 04:54.381
Sponge on a stick.

04:54.424 --> 04:55.749
What's your approach
to dissecting...

04:55.773 --> 04:56.818
Retrograde or antegrade?

04:56.861 --> 04:58.210
Antegrade.

04:58.254 --> 04:59.821
Once I've located
the porta hepatis.

04:59.864 --> 05:02.606
I think Carly was comfortable.

05:02.650 --> 05:03.912
Why does it matter

05:03.955 --> 05:06.218
what kind of questions
are asked when?

05:06.262 --> 05:08.133
Aren't the answers
what's important?

05:08.177 --> 05:09.570
I'm sure you're right.Yes.

05:09.613 --> 05:11.746
What is the plan
for the next date?

05:11.789 --> 05:13.400
Hmm.

05:13.443 --> 05:16.533
We didn't make another date.

05:16.577 --> 05:18.579
Then I grasp gallbladder fundus

05:18.622 --> 05:20.189
and elevate it which way? S-Superiorly.

05:20.232 --> 05:21.799
Is that significant?

05:21.843 --> 05:22.887
No follow-up date?

05:22.931 --> 05:24.541
Not necessarily.

05:24.585 --> 05:25.847
How did the night end?

05:25.890 --> 05:26.978
Good-night kiss?

05:27.022 --> 05:29.241
I've exposed
the triangle of Calot

05:29.285 --> 05:31.722
and ligated the cystic duct
and artery.

05:31.766 --> 05:33.289
What is the risk
at this juncture?

05:33.333 --> 05:35.006
Lacerating the liver
during dissection. Correct.

05:35.030 --> 05:36.336
We didn't kiss.

05:36.379 --> 05:38.076
Ironically, a complication

05:38.120 --> 05:40.818
which I've inadvertently
just demonstrated.

05:40.862 --> 05:42.037
Hold direct pressure.

05:42.080 --> 05:43.255
I need better exposure.

05:43.299 --> 05:45.736
I sliced instead of peeled.

05:45.780 --> 05:46.800
You are familiar
with the Pringle procedure,

05:46.824 --> 05:48.217
Dr. Browne?

05:48.260 --> 05:49.174
Yes, although I've never...

05:49.218 --> 05:50.437
Clamp down the portal triad

05:50.480 --> 05:52.526
with an atraumatic
hemostat clamp,

05:52.569 --> 05:53.889
then use a number 2
catgut suture.

05:55.224 --> 05:57.226
♪♪

06:02.187 --> 06:04.189
♪♪

06:09.325 --> 06:12.241
Shaun, just go to her
and explain.

06:12.284 --> 06:14.896
If what I said
made her uncomfortable,

06:14.939 --> 06:17.246
then saying more
could make her
more uncomfortable.

06:17.289 --> 06:19.204
I sliced instead of peeled.

06:20.205 --> 06:21.816
After Michelle's surgery,

06:21.859 --> 06:23.905
I will go and talk to Carly.

06:23.948 --> 06:26.342
Good.

06:31.129 --> 06:33.784
You can talk to her soon.

06:33.828 --> 06:35.351
OR 2 had a cancellation.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.571
Your surgery is in 45 minutes.

06:41.270 --> 06:42.445
Hi, I'm Dr. Browne.

06:42.489 --> 06:43.988
I will be performing
Michelle's surgery.

06:44.012 --> 06:47.581
♪♪

06:47.624 --> 06:49.191
I will be removing
her gallbladder.

06:49.234 --> 06:51.454
It is a simple procedure.

06:51.498 --> 06:52.823
We're gonna make sure
your daughter

06:52.847 --> 06:54.065
is well taken care of.

06:55.893 --> 06:57.373
Ow!

06:57.417 --> 06:59.593
Sir, we need to decapitate it.

06:59.636 --> 07:01.246
No, don't.
I'm begging you.

07:01.290 --> 07:02.683
Don't.

07:02.726 --> 07:03.814
Please.

07:04.728 --> 07:06.077
I can't get an image.

07:06.121 --> 07:07.165
How did that...

07:07.209 --> 07:08.602
I-Is that a swordfish?

07:08.645 --> 07:10.517
With that dorsal fin?
It's a marlin.

07:10.560 --> 07:12.083
I hooked him
with a naked ballyhoo.

07:12.127 --> 07:13.911
Battled me for over an hour.

07:13.955 --> 07:16.653
Suddenly, he just
leapt out of the water.
He came right at me.

07:16.697 --> 07:18.350
Save the story
for the bar, Quint.

07:18.394 --> 07:19.893
Right now, we need to cut
the damn thing in half.

07:19.917 --> 07:21.658
No.
40-plus years

07:21.702 --> 07:23.062
I've been
chasing a fish like this.

07:23.094 --> 07:24.705
You can't just behead him!

07:24.748 --> 07:25.856
Can't leave his nose
in your leg, either.

07:25.880 --> 07:27.229
His bill.

07:28.535 --> 07:32.190
Can't you just
pull him out gently?

07:32.234 --> 07:33.409
I'll sign a waiver.

07:33.453 --> 07:34.889
The pull-out method never works.

07:34.932 --> 07:37.848
If any of your blood vessels
are damaged, it gets messy.

07:37.892 --> 07:39.435
Congrats. I hear your surgery
is on the schedule.

07:39.459 --> 07:40.982
How's his distal pulse?

07:41.025 --> 07:42.176
A little thready,
but still there.

07:42.200 --> 07:43.375
We need to get him to an MRI.

07:43.419 --> 07:44.979
I'm not going anywhere
without Franklin.

07:47.249 --> 07:48.903
I named him after my father.

07:48.946 --> 07:50.252
You and Franklin both won't fit.

07:51.340 --> 07:52.863
Aah! Oh! Oh!

07:52.907 --> 07:55.344
How? You said he was dead!
I didn't take a pulse.

07:55.387 --> 07:56.495
Go get something to kill it.

07:56.519 --> 07:58.434
No, it's dead! It's moving!

07:58.478 --> 07:59.696
It's a postmortem response.

07:59.740 --> 08:01.481
You guys are doctors.
Don't people do this?

08:01.524 --> 08:02.524
No!
No!

08:08.662 --> 08:09.682
I'll help you review at lunch.

08:09.706 --> 08:12.100
Surgery's in 20 minutes.

08:12.143 --> 08:13.971
Good luck. You, too.

08:25.679 --> 08:28.377
I want to...

08:28.420 --> 08:29.465
No, no, I haven't looked.

08:29.509 --> 08:32.729
I want to be...

08:32.773 --> 08:33.817
Great....great...

08:33.861 --> 08:34.948
Okay.

08:34.991 --> 08:36.385
Or nothing.Nothing.

08:36.428 --> 08:38.909
Got it. I'll be back
as soon as I can.

08:41.477 --> 08:43.392
Hi. You must be
Michelle's mother.

08:43.434 --> 08:44.915
I'm Dr. Browne.
I'll be...

08:44.959 --> 08:46.458
Yeah. How long will
she have to stay in here?

08:46.482 --> 08:48.005
Hospitals make me nervous.

08:48.049 --> 08:50.312
Three days to a week,
depending on...

08:50.355 --> 08:52.836
Well, she's gonna miss
a lot of school.

08:52.880 --> 08:55.360
And she watches Tisha
and her brothers
in the afternoon.

08:55.404 --> 08:57.556
Your daughter
has a serious infection
in her gallbladder.

08:57.580 --> 08:59.277
She's been experiencing symptoms

08:59.321 --> 09:01.279
on and off for a while now.

09:01.323 --> 09:02.542
She never told me that.

09:03.673 --> 09:05.153
Why didn't you tell me that?

09:06.241 --> 09:07.547
Mama... My point is,

09:07.590 --> 09:09.505
she's been ill for a while,

09:09.549 --> 09:10.985
so her recovery may take...

09:11.028 --> 09:13.161
Mom.

09:13.204 --> 09:14.554
Mom?

09:14.597 --> 09:17.600
P-Please,
my... my chest hurts.

09:17.644 --> 09:18.819
What's wrong?

09:18.862 --> 09:20.231
Her oxygen levels
are dropping.
She's tachycardic.

09:20.255 --> 09:22.213
I need a chest CT, stat.

09:22.692 --> 09:25.042
♪♪

09:28.306 --> 09:29.830
You had a blood clot

09:29.873 --> 09:31.483
in the artery
that feeds your lungs.

09:31.527 --> 09:33.094
It's called
a pulmonary embolism.

09:33.137 --> 09:34.791
This medicine broke it up.

09:34.835 --> 09:36.314
How could that happen?

09:36.358 --> 09:37.489
According to our scan,

09:37.533 --> 09:38.815
it was part of a larger clot
in your leg

09:38.839 --> 09:40.667
that broke off
and traveled there.

09:40.710 --> 09:43.060
As for why
the larger one formed,

09:43.104 --> 09:45.672
when I asked you if you were
taking birth control pills,

09:45.715 --> 09:47.325
you said no.

09:47.369 --> 09:48.370
Was that the truth?

09:49.850 --> 09:52.330
You asked me in front of Tisha.

09:52.374 --> 09:54.681
I'm doing it
with my boyfriend,
and I don't want babies,

09:54.724 --> 09:56.291
so I'm taking
birth control pills.

09:56.334 --> 09:57.442
How long have you been
taking them?

09:57.466 --> 09:59.947
I don't know.
A year?

09:59.990 --> 10:02.079
I'm prescribing condoms
for your boyfriend.

10:02.123 --> 10:04.952
You need to go off the pill
to prevent further clots.

10:04.995 --> 10:08.869
Dr. Browne is gonna
place an IVC filter
via your femoral vein,

10:08.912 --> 10:10.784
in case other parts
of the clot break off.

10:10.827 --> 10:13.147
Your gallbladder surgery's
gonna have to wait
till tomorrow.

10:13.525 --> 10:14.526
What are you doing?

10:16.137 --> 10:17.921
This is where
the catheter goes in.

10:17.965 --> 10:19.967
♪♪

10:23.492 --> 10:25.494
♪♪

10:29.063 --> 10:31.195
How did you get these scars?

10:31.239 --> 10:33.676
I cut myself climbing a fence.

10:33.720 --> 10:35.678
♪♪

10:40.901 --> 10:42.206
Those scars...

10:44.556 --> 10:47.342
They're straight, in a row,

10:47.385 --> 10:48.385
all the same length.

10:50.867 --> 10:52.467
I don't believe
you got them
from a fence.

10:54.349 --> 10:56.264
I don't care what you believe.

11:02.487 --> 11:04.707
Kids who cut,

11:04.751 --> 11:08.755
most of them are really sad,

11:08.798 --> 11:10.844
in a lot of pain,

11:10.887 --> 11:12.386
and they say cutting
makes them feel better.

11:12.410 --> 11:13.716
Is that how it is with you?

11:15.413 --> 11:16.613
I don't want to talk about it.

11:19.591 --> 11:20.941
Okay.

11:43.050 --> 11:44.573
My life sucks, okay?

11:44.616 --> 11:46.749
Tell me how.

11:46.793 --> 11:47.968
Why?

11:48.969 --> 11:50.100
It won't change anything.

11:52.494 --> 11:54.888
Talking might
make you feel better,

11:56.498 --> 11:58.108
and maybe I can help.

12:00.154 --> 12:03.810
I live in a foster home,
but I'm not a foster kid.

12:03.853 --> 12:06.116
I'm a whole mother,
but I've never had a baby.

12:08.510 --> 12:10.904
My mom brought three kids
in our home,

12:10.947 --> 12:13.036
and now it's my job
to take care of them...

12:13.080 --> 12:15.604
Make breakfast,
get the kids dressed,

12:15.647 --> 12:17.040
take them to school,
go to school,

12:17.084 --> 12:18.650
pick them up,
dinner, homework, laundry.

12:18.694 --> 12:19.739
Repeat.

12:20.870 --> 12:22.437
I barely ever leave the house

12:22.480 --> 12:24.569
without a kid attached to me.

12:24.613 --> 12:26.528
Can you help me with that?

12:26.571 --> 12:29.183
♪♪

12:29.226 --> 12:31.011
Michelle wouldn't
hurt herself on purpose.

12:31.054 --> 12:32.142
Michelle is unhappy.

12:32.186 --> 12:33.840
She feels pressure

12:33.883 --> 12:35.363
to look after
her foster siblings,

12:35.406 --> 12:36.451
help out at home...

12:36.494 --> 12:37.614
Yeah, her home life is fine.

12:39.280 --> 12:40.847
I'll talk to her.

12:40.890 --> 12:43.153
It might be helpful
to have her speak
with a psychiatrist.

12:43.980 --> 12:45.199
My daughter is not crazy.

12:45.242 --> 12:47.003
We... We don't
do psychiatrists.
You know that.

12:47.027 --> 12:48.245
That needs to change.

12:48.289 --> 12:49.812
When are you doing her surgery?

12:49.856 --> 12:50.987
Tomorrow. Thank you.

12:52.902 --> 12:54.382
I will speak to my daughter.

12:59.039 --> 13:01.302
Don't.

13:01.345 --> 13:03.305
It's your job
to fix her gallbladder,
not her life.

13:04.261 --> 13:05.959
It's your first surgery.

13:06.002 --> 13:07.002
Don't get distracted.

13:20.538 --> 13:21.713
Have you talked to Carly?

13:23.280 --> 13:24.325
No.

13:26.806 --> 13:28.895
Blood pressure is 62/31.

13:28.938 --> 13:30.220
Your patient
is in cardiac arrest.

13:30.244 --> 13:31.288
I know.

13:32.724 --> 13:35.815
You're practicing
the Pringle maneuver

13:35.858 --> 13:37.425
in the event of a liver bleed?

13:37.468 --> 13:39.340
Yes.

13:41.733 --> 13:43.823
That was better.
Thanks.

13:43.866 --> 13:45.607
Now you can talk to Carly.

13:45.650 --> 13:46.913
I need to practice.

13:50.742 --> 13:53.441
Dr. Lim says

13:53.484 --> 13:56.966
getting away from things
every now and again,

13:57.010 --> 13:59.490
having balance in our lives

13:59.534 --> 14:03.364
can be just as important
to our performance
as practice.

14:03.407 --> 14:06.454
Maybe you should
get some balance
by talking to Carly.

14:06.497 --> 14:07.542
I don't know.

14:09.370 --> 14:11.328
I'm nervous about
my surgery, Shaun.

14:11.372 --> 14:13.069
Practice will make me
less nervous.

14:13.113 --> 14:15.115
That will improve
my performance.

14:17.204 --> 14:18.204
Okay.

14:21.164 --> 14:22.557
Okay.

14:24.037 --> 14:26.517
You should also practice
not causing a liver bleed.

14:26.561 --> 14:29.172
Planning on it.

14:29.216 --> 14:34.221
Also, how you will recover
if you cut the portal vein.

14:34.264 --> 14:37.050
That's potentially fatal.

14:37.093 --> 14:39.966
Or if you perforate
the small bowel,

14:40.009 --> 14:42.098
which could cause sepsis,
leading to death.

14:42.142 --> 14:44.753
Or if you cut
the common bile duct,

14:44.796 --> 14:46.122
which would cause... I'm
gonna go talk to Carly.

14:46.146 --> 14:47.756
Right now?
Right now.

14:47.799 --> 14:49.845
Aren't you still nervous? Nope, all better.

14:49.889 --> 14:53.327
♪♪

14:53.370 --> 14:54.632
What blade for the Kocher?

14:54.676 --> 14:56.199
What?

14:56.243 --> 14:58.854
Incision for the chole...
what blade?

14:58.898 --> 14:59.986
Uh...

15:02.423 --> 15:04.164
10.
Mm-hmm.

15:05.687 --> 15:08.081
No, they won't both
fit in the MRI.

15:08.124 --> 15:10.648
Fish Boy doesn't buy it.

15:10.692 --> 15:12.128
Location of the incision.

15:14.478 --> 15:15.958
Why are you trying to help me?

15:16.002 --> 15:17.873
Lim picked you
for the first surgery.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.744
Everyone knows that makes you

15:19.788 --> 15:21.442
the front-runner
for Chief Resident.

15:21.485 --> 15:22.922
This is me sucking up.

15:25.098 --> 15:26.418
I've never been big
on pretense...

15:30.581 --> 15:31.974
Are you okay?

15:32.018 --> 15:33.138
What the hell just happened?

15:34.890 --> 15:36.433
The marlin must have had
metal in his body...

15:36.457 --> 15:37.588
Lures and stuff.

15:37.632 --> 15:39.721
I think a license plate
flew by me.

15:39.764 --> 15:41.418
Franklin!

15:41.462 --> 15:42.767
Oh, no!

15:42.811 --> 15:43.899
Franklin!

15:43.943 --> 15:46.423
♪♪

15:46.467 --> 15:48.338
Oh, it's okay.

15:48.382 --> 15:49.426
Franklin's okay.

15:49.470 --> 15:51.124
It all came out one side.

15:52.690 --> 15:53.930
It won't show when I mount him.

15:55.824 --> 15:57.149
Well, thank goodness
for small miracles.

15:57.173 --> 15:58.218
Ooh.
Oh!

15:58.261 --> 15:59.349
Ow!

15:59.393 --> 16:00.393
Oh!
Ah!

16:02.265 --> 16:05.007
♪♪

16:05.051 --> 16:06.182
I've got his femoral.

16:06.226 --> 16:07.270
Call the OR.
We're coming.

16:07.314 --> 16:12.275
♪♪

16:12.319 --> 16:17.498
♪♪

16:17.541 --> 16:19.239
Hang on, Dr. Browne.

16:19.282 --> 16:20.718
Just need to make an incision

16:20.762 --> 16:23.852
above and below
the arterial injury site.

16:23.895 --> 16:25.941
We need to clamp the femoral
proximal to the bleed

16:25.985 --> 16:27.725
without clipping
the femoral nerve.

16:27.769 --> 16:30.424
Got it. I feel the nerve
right above my index finger.

16:30.467 --> 16:31.816
One down.

16:31.860 --> 16:33.470
My hand is starting to cramp.

16:33.514 --> 16:35.013
Lean over
this way a little bit.
Rotate your wrist.

16:35.037 --> 16:37.431
Just a little bit more.

16:37.474 --> 16:39.476
♪♪

16:39.520 --> 16:40.782
Let's see if that holds.

16:40.825 --> 16:43.741
♪♪

16:51.880 --> 16:53.664
Go get cleaned up.
We'll take it from here.

16:53.708 --> 16:57.016
♪♪

17:03.370 --> 17:05.285
I wanted to check
the patient's bloodwork.

17:05.328 --> 17:07.242
He's negative for
HIV, Hep B and C.

17:07.287 --> 17:09.157
You don't need
prophylactic meds.

17:12.074 --> 17:14.424
I'm nervous about my surgery.

17:15.817 --> 17:17.252
You'll be fine.

17:19.080 --> 17:20.281
And don't ever say that again.

17:21.387 --> 17:23.564
Why?

17:23.607 --> 17:25.435
Weren't you nervous
before your first lead?

17:25.479 --> 17:26.567
If I was,

17:26.609 --> 17:28.569
I didn't volunteer that
to the Chief of Surgery...

17:29.265 --> 17:31.137
Or anyone.

17:31.180 --> 17:32.486
We're women, we're not white,

17:32.529 --> 17:33.922
and we're surgeons.

17:33.965 --> 17:36.751
Unicorns consider us
a fabled species.

17:36.794 --> 17:39.058
We don't get the luxury
of public insecurity.

17:40.711 --> 17:43.801
I will aspire to repressed
stoicism in the future.

17:43.845 --> 17:46.065
We don't need to be insecure,

17:46.108 --> 17:47.805
because every step of the way,

17:47.849 --> 17:50.069
we've had to be
twice as good
as everybody else.

17:51.157 --> 17:52.549
Suck it up.

17:52.593 --> 17:54.595
You got this.

17:54.638 --> 17:59.687
♪♪

17:59.730 --> 18:01.732
♪♪

18:13.875 --> 18:18.532
♪♪

18:18.575 --> 18:23.189
♪♪

18:25.234 --> 18:31.240
♪♪

18:42.208 --> 18:45.689
Don't forget
we have our session
with Dr. Donovan today.

18:45.733 --> 18:46.951
I won't.

18:54.916 --> 18:56.918
Your patient.
Mm-hmm.

18:56.961 --> 18:58.789
What are they like?

18:58.833 --> 19:01.227
Man, woman, young, old?

19:01.270 --> 19:04.012
Woman.

19:04.055 --> 19:06.754
Girl, actually.

19:06.797 --> 19:11.541
She's tough, smart...
really sad.

19:13.326 --> 19:15.763
Her mom has her taking care
of three foster kids.

19:18.592 --> 19:20.392
At least you were only stuck
looking after me.

19:25.990 --> 19:27.166
How old?

19:27.209 --> 19:29.124
14.

19:29.168 --> 19:32.823
Although she acts a lot older.

19:32.867 --> 19:34.427
She's been having sex
for almost a year.

19:36.131 --> 19:38.394
Well, you were about that age
when you were with Wayne.

19:39.700 --> 19:41.963
I didn't have sex
with Wayne. What?

19:42.006 --> 19:43.704
He was in love with you,

19:43.747 --> 19:46.141
always sniffing
around our place.

19:46.185 --> 19:47.273
Maybe.
He didn't get any.

19:47.316 --> 19:48.404
So, who?

19:48.448 --> 19:50.276
Junior prom guy...
Derek.

19:50.319 --> 19:51.625
Der... No.

19:53.192 --> 19:55.803
I didn't lose my virginity

19:55.846 --> 19:58.632
until sophomore year of college.

19:58.675 --> 20:00.416
What were you hoping for,
a proposal?

20:00.460 --> 20:01.461
No.

20:03.332 --> 20:05.073
I wanted it to be special.

20:08.294 --> 20:10.818
Oh, good for you.

20:10.861 --> 20:12.012
I mean, I wouldn't
have held out...

20:12.036 --> 20:13.429
No....but good for you.

20:13.473 --> 20:15.823
I thought for sure
you and Wayne were doing it.

20:18.086 --> 20:19.696
You were okay with that?

20:19.740 --> 20:21.611
You were so serious.

20:21.655 --> 20:23.396
So restrained.

20:23.439 --> 20:25.963
We talked about birth control.

20:26.007 --> 20:27.487
I figured, "Good for her.

20:27.530 --> 20:29.880
She's finally relaxing,
having some fun."

20:34.015 --> 20:37.497
Well, I was so restrained
and serious

20:37.540 --> 20:39.500
'cause I never knew
when you were
gonna fall apart.

20:44.982 --> 20:45.982
Got to get to work.

20:55.906 --> 20:58.169
I'll be back before
Michelle goes into surgery.

20:58.213 --> 20:59.495
Have you had a chance
to talk to her

20:59.519 --> 21:01.608
about her cutting?

21:01.651 --> 21:04.654
Oh, yeah, some fool friend
of hers gave her the idea.

21:04.698 --> 21:06.700
She's not unhappy.
It's just peer pressure.

21:06.743 --> 21:08.441
She sounded unhappy to me.

21:08.484 --> 21:11.095
She's upset I didn't let her
go hang out with her friends.

21:11.139 --> 21:12.880
It's typical teen drama.

21:12.923 --> 21:14.490
She promised me
she's done cutting.

21:14.534 --> 21:16.362
Self-harming behavior
doesn't just stop.

21:16.405 --> 21:18.668
Michelle might need... Dr. Browne.

21:18.712 --> 21:20.235
My daughter
needs to have surgery

21:20.279 --> 21:21.454
and get out of this hospital.

21:35.424 --> 21:37.296
You didn't tell your mom
the truth

21:37.339 --> 21:40.342
about why you cut yourself,

21:40.386 --> 21:41.604
about how unhappy you are.

21:41.648 --> 21:43.214
I tried.

21:43.258 --> 21:44.520
She didn't want to hear it,

21:44.564 --> 21:46.914
just said that things aren't
always gonna go my way

21:46.957 --> 21:49.003
and I need to be
more responsible.

21:49.046 --> 21:50.700
Like I'm not already.

22:04.105 --> 22:06.977
Growing up, I had
to take care of my mom.

22:07.021 --> 22:08.152
What was wrong with her?

22:08.196 --> 22:09.806
She's mentally ill.

22:09.850 --> 22:11.417
Bipolar disorder

22:11.460 --> 22:14.158
and a drinking problem, pills.

22:14.202 --> 22:15.377
When things were bad,

22:15.421 --> 22:18.467
she'd forget to buy groceries

22:18.511 --> 22:21.818
or clean the trailer
or pick me up.

22:21.862 --> 22:25.866
Or she'd spend all our rent
on something stupid.

22:25.909 --> 22:28.347
And I thought

22:28.390 --> 22:31.654
if I could make her life
easy enough...

22:31.698 --> 22:35.049
If I cooked and cleaned
and got good grades...

22:35.092 --> 22:37.094
Then she'd get better.

22:37.138 --> 22:39.053
But she never did.

22:39.096 --> 22:41.621
And for the longest time,

22:41.664 --> 22:43.797
I thought it was my fault
she was sick.

22:43.840 --> 22:46.756
And I probably still would

22:46.800 --> 22:49.411
if a psychiatrist
hadn't refused to believe me

22:49.455 --> 22:52.458
when I said I was fine.

22:54.285 --> 22:55.809
You've been to a psychiatrist?

22:55.852 --> 22:59.508
♪♪

22:59.552 --> 23:01.945
But you're, like,
a fancy surgeon.

23:04.600 --> 23:07.603
♪♪

23:07.647 --> 23:09.692
I could have a therapist
come by and see you

23:09.736 --> 23:10.693
before your surgery.

23:10.737 --> 23:16.786
♪♪

23:16.830 --> 23:22.705
♪♪

23:22.749 --> 23:24.228
Okay.

23:24.272 --> 23:28.581
♪♪

23:40.984 --> 23:42.682
He should be getting better.

23:42.725 --> 23:44.858
It's got to be an infection
from the marlin.

23:44.901 --> 23:47.513
Aeromonas
or mycobacterium marinum.

23:47.556 --> 23:49.515
Would've responded
to the antibiotics.

23:49.558 --> 23:52.605
Guys, I'm trying to focus.

23:52.648 --> 23:56.347
What if he has an underlying
autoimmune disorder?

23:56.391 --> 23:57.760
It could've been triggered
by the surgery

23:57.784 --> 23:59.873
or even the initial
fish stabbing.

23:59.916 --> 24:02.179
It would explain why
the leg ulcerations
are progressing

24:02.223 --> 24:03.485
despite good arterial flow.

24:03.529 --> 24:05.835
We could see
if he responds to steroids.

24:05.879 --> 24:08.229
Which could kill him
if it is an infection.

24:08.272 --> 24:12.799
♪♪

24:12.842 --> 24:14.844
But we could run an ANA,
see if he's positive.

24:16.106 --> 24:17.543
What about a parasite?

24:17.586 --> 24:20.328
Rhinosporidium seeberi
or a gill worm.

24:20.371 --> 24:22.069
Have you talked to Carly?

24:22.112 --> 24:23.549
Sorry.

24:23.592 --> 24:25.333
I got sidetracked by a marlin.

24:25.376 --> 24:28.858
♪♪

24:30.904 --> 24:33.123
♪♪

24:39.826 --> 24:41.044
Come in.

24:41.088 --> 24:43.438
You wanted to see me?

24:43.482 --> 24:45.788
Ms. Reynolds tells me
that you went
against her wishes

24:45.832 --> 24:47.672
and had her daughter
speak with a psychiatrist.

24:48.835 --> 24:53.187
Uh, Michelle asked
to see a therapist.

24:53.230 --> 24:55.711
Only after
you talked her into it.

24:55.755 --> 24:57.384
I'm gonna report you
to the medical board.

24:57.408 --> 24:58.497
You had no right...

24:58.540 --> 25:00.673
Dr. Browne,
were you concerned

25:00.716 --> 25:02.716
that Michelle might be
a serious danger to herself?

25:02.979 --> 25:04.372
Yes.

25:04.415 --> 25:05.939
In that case,
the consult was required.

25:05.982 --> 25:07.636
That said,

25:07.680 --> 25:11.118
Dr. Browne's failure
to inform you
was inappropriate.

25:11.161 --> 25:12.598
You're off the case.

25:12.641 --> 25:15.078
Dr. Melendez
will perform the surgery.

25:15.122 --> 25:19.387
♪♪

25:24.566 --> 25:26.176
How are you doing?

25:27.221 --> 25:28.701
Claire?

25:28.744 --> 25:30.311
I understand today's
a big day for you.

25:30.354 --> 25:32.269
Your first surgery.

25:32.313 --> 25:33.183
We don't need
to talk about that.

25:33.227 --> 25:35.838
Hmm, I think we do.

25:35.882 --> 25:37.990
You've been taking care of
your mother for a long time.

25:38.014 --> 25:40.364
That's a pattern you both
need to break out of.

25:43.324 --> 25:44.867
I know I haven't always
been there for you,

25:44.891 --> 25:46.719
and I just... I...

25:46.762 --> 25:47.807
I'm trying to change that.

25:47.850 --> 25:49.460
I know, Mom.

25:49.504 --> 25:50.612
I'm good.
Everything is fine.

25:50.636 --> 25:51.767
And your first surgery?

25:51.811 --> 25:53.813
Is that this afternoon?

25:53.856 --> 25:54.856
It's...

25:56.729 --> 25:57.991
Actually, it's not.

25:58.034 --> 25:59.514
Um...

26:00.863 --> 26:02.604
I arranged a psych consult

26:02.648 --> 26:04.650
without the mother's permission,

26:04.693 --> 26:06.608
so I got thrown off the case.

26:06.652 --> 26:08.088
How could the hospital
allow that?

26:08.131 --> 26:09.219
What is wrong with them?

26:09.263 --> 26:10.632
After how hard
you've worked, I just...

26:10.656 --> 26:13.049
It's okay, Mom.
They kind of had to.

26:13.093 --> 26:14.157
That must be
a big disappointment...

26:14.181 --> 26:15.574
It is.

26:19.229 --> 26:20.753
Anything else, Claire?

26:23.451 --> 26:25.758
I'm upset, humiliated,

26:27.586 --> 26:30.850
so, so mad
at my patient's mother

26:30.893 --> 26:32.329
for not taking care
of her daughter.

26:35.724 --> 26:37.944
And I...
I'm relieved.

26:37.987 --> 26:40.642
I'm so, so relieved
to have that weight off of me,

26:40.686 --> 26:42.296
and that makes me
feel like a fraud.

26:42.339 --> 26:43.384
Don't you say that.

26:43.427 --> 26:44.820
How can I be so scared

26:44.864 --> 26:47.823
to do something
I've wanted for so long?

26:47.867 --> 26:50.478
Because things that matter
are scary.

26:52.045 --> 26:54.830
That's how I feel
about coming here,

26:54.874 --> 26:57.659
talking about my life
and our relationship.

26:59.182 --> 27:00.182
What if I can't fix it?

27:02.490 --> 27:03.709
What if I can't make up

27:03.752 --> 27:05.624
for all the times
I've let you down?

27:07.582 --> 27:08.801
And then I think...

27:11.499 --> 27:13.675
"Just be like Claire."

27:13.719 --> 27:17.723
♪♪

27:17.766 --> 27:21.509
Because nothing
stops you... ever.

27:21.552 --> 27:23.032
You see what you want,

27:23.076 --> 27:25.426
and you go after it
with everything you've got.

27:25.469 --> 27:27.341
♪♪

27:27.384 --> 27:28.864
You are an inspiration.

27:31.345 --> 27:33.042
You're myinspiration.

27:33.086 --> 27:35.001
♪♪

27:41.790 --> 27:46.055
♪♪

27:46.099 --> 27:47.404
Carly?

27:47.448 --> 27:48.841
Hi.
Do you have a second?

27:48.884 --> 27:50.103
OR 2 is waiting to learn

27:50.146 --> 27:52.409
the patient's mass
wasn't cancerous
so they can close.

27:52.453 --> 27:53.280
I can come back after.

27:53.323 --> 27:54.411
I'll be at the cafe?

27:54.455 --> 27:56.065
Mm-hmm.
Okay.

27:56.109 --> 27:58.677
Anesthesiology, line 271.

27:58.720 --> 28:01.723
Anesthesiology, call line 271.

28:01.767 --> 28:06.641
♪♪

28:06.685 --> 28:08.121
Cancer.

28:08.164 --> 28:09.949
The marlin guy has cancer.

28:09.992 --> 28:11.864
CT chest, abdomen,
and pelvis
showed no masses.

28:11.907 --> 28:13.648
It's in his leg.

28:13.692 --> 28:15.345
It explains
progressive ulcerations

28:15.389 --> 28:16.782
despite good arterial flow.

28:16.825 --> 28:18.827
And why the antibiotics
aren't working.

28:18.871 --> 28:20.871
We'll send a tissue sample
from the ulcerated area.

28:22.875 --> 28:25.181
And when I'mChief Resident,
I'll remember this.

28:29.620 --> 28:30.534
There's a problem with Michelle.

28:30.578 --> 28:31.753
I'm not doing it!

28:31.797 --> 28:33.233
You need to calm down.

28:33.276 --> 28:34.800
You don't get
to tell me what to do!

28:34.843 --> 28:36.366
I want Dr. Browne!

28:36.410 --> 28:37.716
Michelle?
What's going on?

28:37.759 --> 28:39.892
I want you to do my surgery.

28:39.935 --> 28:41.545
I want her, Mama,
not somebody else.

28:41.589 --> 28:43.547
Dr. Melendez
is gonna do your surgery.

28:43.591 --> 28:44.679
He is a great doctor.

28:44.723 --> 28:45.898
He's not you.

28:45.941 --> 28:47.203
Y-You care about me.

28:47.247 --> 28:49.292
Everybody here cares
about you, Michelle.

28:49.336 --> 28:51.488
Now, please sit down.
You could rupture
your gallbladder.

28:51.512 --> 28:53.644
I-I-I don't want to get better.

28:53.688 --> 28:55.734
Don't say that. It's the truth!

28:55.777 --> 28:57.257
Michelle, you need this surgery.

28:57.300 --> 28:59.389
That is all that matters...
not whether I do it.

28:59.433 --> 29:01.217
♪♪

29:02.436 --> 29:03.959
I'm gonna be there.

29:04.003 --> 29:05.395
I will be watching
from the gallery

29:05.439 --> 29:06.527
the whole time.

29:09.225 --> 29:12.185
You just... You need...
You need to sit down.

29:12.228 --> 29:13.926
♪♪

29:15.841 --> 29:21.194
♪♪

29:25.807 --> 29:26.982
The kid okay?

29:28.854 --> 29:30.725
I had to pull you off.

29:30.769 --> 29:32.988
If you made even the tiniest
misstep during surgery,

29:33.032 --> 29:34.903
that mom would go
from threat to lawsuit.

29:38.211 --> 29:40.213
Is Patricia okay with me
watching from the gallery?

29:40.256 --> 29:41.344
No.

29:43.346 --> 29:45.266
You can't remove
her gallbladder
from the gallery.

29:45.784 --> 29:46.828
What?

29:46.872 --> 29:48.961
You're doing Michelle's surgery.

29:49.004 --> 29:51.746
How'd you get the mom
to change her mind?

29:51.790 --> 29:54.705
I explained that,
given Dr. Browne's
commitment to her daughter,

29:54.749 --> 29:56.925
she's the perfect choice
to lead the surgery.

29:56.969 --> 29:58.969
Especially with me
over her shoulder
the whole time.

30:02.104 --> 30:03.671
Thank you for fighting for me.

30:03.714 --> 30:04.672
That's what bosses do.

30:04.715 --> 30:05.891
Let's go.

30:05.934 --> 30:11.113
♪♪

30:11.157 --> 30:16.292
♪♪

30:16.336 --> 30:18.773
You stood me up.
Sorry about that.

30:18.817 --> 30:20.557
What's up?

30:20.601 --> 30:23.082
Shaun's a little worried
he may have freaked you out

30:23.125 --> 30:25.693
with his... questionnaire
the other night.

30:25.736 --> 30:27.347
Oh, I thought it was cool.

30:27.390 --> 30:28.759
Small talk
bores the hell out of me.

30:28.783 --> 30:30.480
Well, then, great.

30:30.524 --> 30:32.395
I'll tell him.

30:32.439 --> 30:34.920
Shaun got worried about that
all on his own?

30:34.963 --> 30:36.043
That doesn't seem like him.

30:37.444 --> 30:39.141
I may have mentioned

30:39.185 --> 30:41.796
that people don't usually ask
deeply personal questions

30:41.840 --> 30:42.841
on an early date.

30:45.147 --> 30:46.932
Claire, I like you,

30:46.975 --> 30:48.411
but we don't really know
each other.

30:48.455 --> 30:50.370
And yet you decided

30:50.413 --> 30:52.720
how I was going to react
to Shaun's questions,

30:52.763 --> 30:55.070
which isn't your business.

30:55.114 --> 30:56.332
And you were wrong...

30:56.376 --> 30:59.161
Totally, totally wrong.

30:59.205 --> 31:01.685
Shaun and I don't need you
or anyone else

31:01.729 --> 31:05.080
to run interference
on our relationship.

31:05.124 --> 31:06.212
Butt out.

31:16.700 --> 31:18.702
♪♪

31:25.753 --> 31:27.755
♪♪

31:35.676 --> 31:37.678
♪♪

31:43.292 --> 31:45.338
♪♪

31:55.348 --> 32:00.657
♪♪

32:00.701 --> 32:06.446
♪♪

32:06.489 --> 32:08.448
Is everybody ready
for a Time Out?

32:08.491 --> 32:10.711
♪♪

32:10.754 --> 32:14.193
Dr. Claire Browne,
lead surgeon.

32:14.236 --> 32:16.021
Dr. Neil Melendez,
attending surgeon.

32:16.064 --> 32:18.937
Dr. Shaun Murphy,
assisting.

32:18.980 --> 32:22.027
Dr. Jan Lancaster,
anesthesia.

32:22.070 --> 32:24.116
Donna Petringa, scrub nurse.

32:24.159 --> 32:26.814
Shani Walden, circulating nurse.

32:26.857 --> 32:28.990
Patient is Michelle Reynolds.

32:29.034 --> 32:31.471
We will be performing
an open cholecystectomy.

32:31.514 --> 32:34.039
All tools I need
are confirmed to be present.

32:34.082 --> 32:36.780
Estimated blood loss, 100 cc.

32:36.824 --> 32:39.000
Patient will go to the ICU
after surgery.

32:39.044 --> 32:40.610
Is everybody in agreement?

32:42.961 --> 32:45.093
Dr. Murphy, have you
ChloraPrepped the site?

32:45.615 --> 32:46.747
I have.

32:48.053 --> 32:49.141
10 blade.

32:49.184 --> 32:51.404
♪♪

32:54.320 --> 32:56.191
♪♪

33:02.589 --> 33:05.113
♪♪

33:10.901 --> 33:13.165
♪♪

33:19.475 --> 33:20.346
Sponge.

33:20.389 --> 33:22.391
♪♪

33:28.136 --> 33:30.095
Top layer of abdominal muscle
is exposed.

33:30.138 --> 33:31.418
I'll need a Bovie
to cut through.

33:31.444 --> 33:36.623
♪♪

33:36.666 --> 33:42.107
♪♪

33:42.150 --> 33:48.939
♪♪

33:48.983 --> 33:50.593
Nice work,
Dr. Browne.

33:50.637 --> 33:53.988
♪♪

33:54.032 --> 33:55.337
Bookwalter Retractor.

33:55.381 --> 33:57.383
♪♪

34:02.823 --> 34:04.433
I see the liver,

34:04.477 --> 34:06.696
and I need to better expose
the inferior surface.

34:06.740 --> 34:08.306
Retract the duodenum
inferiorly, please.

34:12.440 --> 34:14.487
Gallbladder exposed.

34:14.530 --> 34:16.532
♪♪

34:24.062 --> 34:25.411
Dr. Browne?

34:28.065 --> 34:30.545
There is more scarring
than the imaging suggested.

34:30.590 --> 34:31.938
True.

34:32.983 --> 34:36.335
♪♪

34:36.378 --> 34:37.726
Talk through your approach.

34:40.643 --> 34:44.908
I... grasp
the gallbladder fundus forward

34:44.952 --> 34:47.302
and use a right-angle clamp
in my suction

34:47.346 --> 34:49.956
to develop a plane
around the gallbladder.

34:50.000 --> 34:51.393
Kelly clamp,

34:51.437 --> 34:52.916
a right-angle clamp,
and suction.

34:52.960 --> 34:54.918
♪♪

35:06.234 --> 35:08.802
♪♪

35:13.981 --> 35:17.332
That was elegant use
of the Kelly clamp.

35:17.376 --> 35:19.552
♪♪

35:22.772 --> 35:24.687
I see the cystic duct

35:24.731 --> 35:27.168
and, behind it,
the cystic artery.

35:27.212 --> 35:29.518
I need my first assist
to confirm

35:29.562 --> 35:31.303
that I have identified
the common bile duct

35:31.346 --> 35:32.608
and it is out of the way.

35:32.652 --> 35:33.870
Yes.

35:33.914 --> 35:35.437
Cutting the duct would be...

35:35.481 --> 35:36.569
Very, very bad.

35:37.918 --> 35:40.138
Move the gallbladder
cranially a little bit.

35:41.400 --> 35:42.705
Titanium clip applier.

35:42.749 --> 35:45.273
♪♪

35:51.497 --> 35:53.412
♪♪

35:59.940 --> 36:01.463
You sure you have a clear view?

36:01.507 --> 36:04.988
♪♪

36:05.032 --> 36:06.164
Making the cut.

36:07.513 --> 36:11.038
♪♪

36:14.998 --> 36:17.740
♪♪

36:22.528 --> 36:25.183
♪♪

36:31.841 --> 36:32.973
She's hemorrhaging.

36:33.016 --> 36:37.195
♪♪

36:37.238 --> 36:38.737
I can't see
the source of the bleeding.

36:38.761 --> 36:41.808
♪♪

36:46.465 --> 36:49.032
MAP is 45 and dropping.

36:51.121 --> 36:56.953
♪♪

37:00.218 --> 37:01.610
What do you think is happening?

37:04.657 --> 37:06.049
Most likely,

37:06.093 --> 37:09.531
my scissors' tip nicked
the right hepatic artery.

37:09.575 --> 37:10.750
It happens.

37:10.793 --> 37:11.793
It's happened to me.

37:15.363 --> 37:18.018
I need to clamp
the common hepatic artery,

37:18.061 --> 37:19.411
repair the arterial wall

37:19.454 --> 37:21.108
with running
6-0 Prolene sutures.

37:21.151 --> 37:22.936
That's what I would do.

37:24.938 --> 37:27.070
♪♪

37:31.336 --> 37:33.381
♪♪

37:36.950 --> 37:38.952
♪♪

37:55.708 --> 37:58.363
♪♪

38:02.758 --> 38:05.326
♪♪

38:12.725 --> 38:14.596
Hey, hey, hey.
Slow down. Slow down.

38:14.640 --> 38:16.119
No running.
No running.

38:17.556 --> 38:19.514
Dr. Browne,
how's my daughter?

38:19.558 --> 38:21.037
The surgery was a success,

38:21.081 --> 38:22.604
and we expect a full recovery.

38:24.258 --> 38:26.173
I wanna see her!

38:27.740 --> 38:29.307
Is that okay?

38:29.350 --> 38:30.873
Yay!
Okay.

38:36.662 --> 38:38.707
Michelle says
she wants to be a doctor.

38:41.231 --> 38:43.146
She would be a great one.

38:45.279 --> 38:48.369
Uh, that therapist
Michelle talked to...

38:50.066 --> 38:52.373
could I get her card?

38:55.811 --> 38:58.031
♪♪

38:58.074 --> 39:00.338
Hi, baby.Hey.

39:07.997 --> 39:14.134
♪♪

39:14.177 --> 39:15.614
Okay.

39:15.657 --> 39:17.224
♪♪

39:17.267 --> 39:19.226
Three, two, one.

39:24.187 --> 39:25.928
You were right.

39:25.972 --> 39:27.974
He had angiosarcoma of the leg.

39:28.017 --> 39:30.629
Had to amputate,
but the margins were clean.

39:30.672 --> 39:32.239
Hmm.
What happened to the...

39:32.282 --> 39:33.283
Franklin!

39:34.067 --> 39:36.939
Oh!

39:36.983 --> 39:39.594
♪♪

39:39.638 --> 39:42.989
Franklin, you amazing fish!

39:43.946 --> 39:45.513
You saved my life.

39:45.557 --> 39:47.167
Come on, bring him...
bring him here.

39:47.210 --> 39:48.821
Bring him...
Bring him in.

39:48.864 --> 39:49.952
Oh.

39:51.998 --> 39:57.220
♪♪

39:57.264 --> 39:58.439
Thank you, guys.

39:58.483 --> 40:01.224
Group hug.

40:01.268 --> 40:06.926
♪♪

40:06.969 --> 40:08.667
Do you prefer to work in a team

40:08.710 --> 40:12.105
or do you prefer to lead
or follow command?

40:12.148 --> 40:15.021
Team... and to lead.

40:18.938 --> 40:21.201
What machine
or appliance in your house

40:21.244 --> 40:22.985
aggravates you the most?

40:23.029 --> 40:24.029
The dishwasher.

40:30.123 --> 40:31.777
Hey, I'm just leaving.

40:32.908 --> 40:34.693
Who is this?

40:41.743 --> 40:47.662
♪♪

40:47.706 --> 40:53.668
♪♪

40:53.712 --> 40:56.715
♪ From the greatest height

40:56.758 --> 41:01.633
♪♪

41:01.676 --> 41:04.505
♪ Slow motion life

41:04.549 --> 41:09.597
♪♪

41:09.641 --> 41:15.690
♪ You know I'd pay to leave
these tears behind

41:15.734 --> 41:17.866
♪ But it's fine

41:17.910 --> 41:20.347
♪ I know we're all the same

41:20.390 --> 41:26.092
♪♪

41:26.135 --> 41:28.529
♪ Slow motion pain

41:28.573 --> 41:33.839
♪♪

41:33.882 --> 41:39.192
♪ Now it's all blood
in the open

41:39.235 --> 41:43.022
♪ But we're not scared

41:43.065 --> 41:44.763
Message received

41:44.806 --> 41:48.941
at 5:30 p.m. from Mom.

41:50.856 --> 41:52.814
Hey, baby, I got your text.

41:52.858 --> 41:54.729
See, I knew it was just
a temporary setback.

41:54.773 --> 41:56.165
We're gonna celebrate.

41:56.209 --> 41:57.558
I made dinner.

41:57.602 --> 41:59.168
And I'm gonna
go get some dessert.

41:59.212 --> 42:00.692
I'll see you soon.

42:00.735 --> 42:02.563
I'm so proud of you, baby.

